[SN]TITLE[SN]
Anders Lindegaard: Preston sign West Brom goalkeeper on loan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Championship side Preston North End have signed goalkeeper Anders Lindegaard on loan from West Bromwich Albion for the remainder of the season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Denmark international Lindegaard, 31, has played only one League Cup game since joining the Baggies on a free transfer from Manchester United.
United have chosen to recall Sam Johnstone, who started Saturday's 3-1 home defeat by Brentford at Deepdale.
Lindegaard could make his Preston debut at Derby on 2 February.
